The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques such as graph convolutional networks and learned differentiable models for molecular optimization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the problem of targeted molecular design is related to computational drug discovery, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
